==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: broad-minded
<hw>broad-minded</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>incapable of
being shocked. Opposite of <ant>shockable</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> unshockable.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>inclined to respect views and beliefs that differ
from one's own. Opposite of <ant>narrow-minded</ant>.</def> [Narrower
terms: <stype>free-thinking, latitudinarian, undogmatic,
undogmatical</stype>]⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> broadminded, broad, liberal, tolerant, open-minded,
open.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Broadmouth</ent>⟦br⟧
